## ததஅக

[ upavācam ]  
  
பெ. upavāsa.fast  
fasting; உண்ணா விரதம். இதன் புனலாடி யுபவாச முஞற்றியக்கால் (சேதுபு. பலதீ. 19)  
s. fast  
fasting  
s. a fast comprising abstinence from food and drink  
and in some cases  
also from venery  
from the use of a matrass or mat  
c. when sleeping  
and even from sleep. it is connected with the observance of religious duties: some fasts are continued for nine days in suc cession with only a little water  
milk or fruit occasionally taken  
உணவொழிக்கை  
2. a firealtar  
ஓமபீடம். wils. p  
158. upa vasa  
